10 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
11 An Act relating to state government; requiring
certain notification to successor; requiring
12 notification to indicate start of absence and
anticipated return; directing notice to be made
13 twenty-four hours before absence except for
emergencies; providing for codification; and
14 providing an effective date.
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 8.20 of Title 74, unless there
20 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21 Notification, as provided in this section, shall be required
22 when the Governor is absent from the state. Except in the event of
23 an emergency, at least twenty-four (24) hours prior to the Governor
24 being absent from the state, the Governor shall provide electronic
HB4434 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 noti fication to the Lieutenant Governor of his or her plans to be
2 absent from the state, indicating the start date and time and the
3 anticipated return date and time in such notification. The
4 notification required by this section shall also be required of the
5 acting Governor, when he or she is absent from the state, and follow
6 the line of succession provided in Section 15 of Article VI of the
7 Oklahoma Constitution or as may be provided by law. In the event of
8 an emergency, notice shall be provided prior to being absent from
9 the state.
10 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective January 11, 2027.
11
